@node help_main_file "IFF-File"
@prev help_main_height
@next help_main_list

  Hotkey..: i,I

  Here you must enter the destination-path for the image-file.
  Please make sure that there is no existing file with the same
  path because in this it will be overwritten without any comment.

@endnode

@node help_main_list ""
@prev help_main_file
@next help_main_countdown

  Hotkey..: None

  This list shows you all available screens or windows. You can
  switch between screens and windows by pressing the cursor-keys.
  You can switch between the list by pressing the space-key.
  Each time you do that, the list will also be refreshed.

  Other keys:

    CURSOR UP           : moves to the entry above
    CURSOR DOWN         : moves to the entry below
  
    CUSOR UP    + SHIFT : moves to the top of the page
    CUSOR DOWN  + SHIFT : moves to the bottom of the page

    CURSOR UP   + CTRL  : moves to the first entry
    CURSOR DOWN + CTRL  : moves to the last entry

@endnode


@node help_main_countdown "Countdown"
@prev help_main_list
@next help_main_activate

  Hotkey..: c,C

  I've implemented this feature because it was requester by an user
  and I think it's useful. In this field you can enter the number
  of seconds my program have to wait before grabbing. This is useful
  for you if you want to activate a window or something else before
  the grabbing process starts.

@endnode


@node help_main_activate "Activate window"
@prev help_main_countdown
@next glo_howtouse

  Hotkey..: a,A

  This is also a new and useful feature. If this checkbox is selected
  the selected window will be activated before the picture will be saved.
  Make sure you don't run a commodity like AutoPoint because this 
  could deactivate the window before it will be saved.

@endnode
